# Flutter Migration Changelog Rule

After completing any code change (new feature, bug fix, refactor, UI update, new route, etc.), append an entry to `flutterchanges.md` at the top of the **Changes** section.

## Entry format

```markdown
### YYYY-MM-DD — Short title of the change

**Files changed:** `src/pages/Foo.tsx`, `src/components/Bar.tsx`, ...

**What changed (React/TS):**
- Bullet summary of what was added or modified.

**Flutter migration notes:**
- Which Flutter widgets, packages, or patterns to use.
- Any new routes to register in `go_router`.
- Any new Supabase calls to replicate via `supabase_flutter`.
- Any new state/context to set up in Riverpod/Bloc.
- UI specifics: layout widgets, theming, animations.
```

## Rules

- Always place the newest entry directly under the `<!-- New entries -->` comment.
- Reference the tech stack mapping table at the top of the file for consistent package choices.
- Be specific: name the exact Flutter widget or package, not just "use Flutter equivalent."
- If the change is purely a bug fix with no structural impact, still log it but note "No new Flutter migration work — fix the equivalent logic in Dart."
- If new dependencies were added to `package.json`, note the Flutter counterpart package and version to add to `pubspec.yaml`.
